results.name: David Caesar
results.biography:
David Caesar (born 1963) is an Australian television and film director and writer. He grew up in Turlinjah on the south coast of NSW and attended school in nearby Moruya where he was school captain in his senior year.

Caesar graduated from the Australian Film Television and Radio School in 1987. He won an AWGIE and best director at Shanghai Film Festival for his film MULLET.  He won a Queensland Premiers Literary award for the screenplay for PRIME MOVER in 2008. Source: Wikidata; 01/08/2023
